Subject: [PATCH] refactor: split main.py and research_tasks.py into modules
 under 150 lines

Extract main.py (1035 LOC) into src/runner/ package: run_folder, chapters,
figures (+figure_styles_a/b/c), sanitize (+structure/content/final), tex_math,
compile, finalize, dryrun. Extract research_tasks.py (854 LOC) into focused
task modules. Both originals become thin re-export shims so all existing
imports (src/graph/nodes.py, src/crew.py, tests) keep working unchanged.

Behavior preserved verbatim. compile_pdf gains UTF-8 decoding + a timeout
guard for Windows. All 143 tests pass; dry-run reproduces identical output.
